node.text:
From the exclusive partnership between @jacobandco and @bugatti - Here is the Chiron Tourbillon 💣

This watch is designed to honor the iconic Bugatti Chiron. It features a movement that looks like the iconic Bugatti 16-cylinder engine. 
By pushing the crown on the right hand side the engine comes to life. 
This watch took almost 1 year to develop and it consists of 578 components.

The Chiron Tourbillon feature a black titanium case that houses a very complicated movement with a 1-minute 30° inclined flying tourbillon, the ”W16 Engine” in a sapphire block and a Power Reserve indicator.

The watch is a limited edition of 250 pieces and priced at $280,000 💸

A true engine on the wrist.

node.text:
The @artisansdegeneve Sea Shepherd Challenge 🌚

A reinterpretation of Captain Paul Watson's Rolex® Submariner® Date. Paul Watson is Sea Shepherd's founder, he has dedicated his life to protect the oceans and marine wildlife.  For this customization, Artisans de Genève realized their very first complication: a moonphase enhanced with an aventurine dial and grand feu disc enamel. To achieve the watchmaking complication, Artisans de Genève added a specific module to the 3135 movement, the caliber beveled, circular-grained and polished by hand. 
-
Artisans de Genève is an independent company specialized in the personalization of timepieces. Artisans de Genève is not affiliated with Rolex SA nor authorized by them to intervene on their products for any reason whatsoever. This personalization was ordered for his private use by a customer who owns a Rolex® timepiece.

node.text:
The Omega De Ville Tourbillon Master Chronometer.

Featuring a complex 43mm case construction where a Sedna gold structure is mounted on a Canapus white gold base. 

The central Torbillon is completely in titanium and black ceramic in the upper side.

Retail price is $165,000 💸
